title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\SslCertificate
name: SslCertificate
description:
Represents an SSL Certificate resource.

Google Compute Engine has two SSL Certificate resources:

  • Global * Regional The sslCertificates are used by:
  • external HTTPS load balancers
  • SSL proxy load balancers The regionSslCertificates are used by internal HTTPS load balancers. Optionally, certificate file contents that you upload can contain a set of up to five PEM-encoded certificates. The API call creates an object (sslCertificate) that holds this data. You can use SSL keys and certificates to secure connections to a load balancer. For more information, read Creating and using SSL certificates, SSL certificates quotas and limits, and Troubleshooting SSL certificates. (== resource_for {$api_version}.sslCertificates ==) (== resource_for {$api_version}.regionSslCertificates ==)

params.name: data.certificate
params.description: A value read into memory from a certificate file. The certificate file must be in PEM format. The certificate chain must be no greater than 5 certs long. The chain must include at least one intermediate cert.

params.name: data.creation_timestamp
params.description: [Output Only] Creation timestamp in RFC3339 text format.

params.description: An optional description of this resource. Provide this property when you create the resource.

params.name: data.expire_time
params.description: [Output Only] Expire time of the certificate. RFC3339

params.name: data.id
params.description: [Output Only] The unique identifier for the resource. This identifier is defined by the server.

params.name: data.kind
params.description: [Output Only] Type of the resource. Always compute#sslCertificate for SSL certificates.

params.name: data.managed
params.description: Configuration and status of a managed SSL certificate.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Name of the resource. Provided by the client when the resource is created. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression [a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])? which means the first character must be a lowercase letter, and all following characters must be a dash, lowercase letter, or digit, except the last character, which cannot be a dash.

params.name: data.private_key
params.description: A value read into memory from a write-only private key file. The private key file must be in PEM format. For security, only insert requests include this field.

params.name: data.region
params.description: [Output Only] URL of the region where the regional SSL Certificate resides. This field is not applicable to global SSL Certificate.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output only] Server-defined URL for the resource.

params.name: data.self_managed
params.description: Configuration and status of a self-managed SSL certificate.

params.name: data.subject_alternative_names
params.description: [Output Only] Domains associated with the certificate via Subject Alternative Name.

params.name: data.type
params.description: (Optional) Specifies the type of SSL certificate, either "SELF_MANAGED" or "MANAGED". If not specified, the certificate is self-managed and the fields certificate and private_key are used.
